Two people have died after a shooting incident at a shopping mall in the east of Pretoria on Friday morning.This is according to Netcare 911, who tweeted that two people had died following the shooting incident.Two people tragically died after a shooting incident at a Shopping mall in Pretoria @ewnupdates @JacaNews @News24 @Beeld_Nuus @garypaul911&mdash; Netcare911 (@Netcare911_sa) March 10, 2017Earlier on Friday, police and paramedics responded in numbers to the shooting incident at the Glenfair shopping centre, the Pretoria East Rekord reports.Scene of shooting.Details were still unclear as police arrived on the scene, where one person was allegedly shot.The shop had since been closed off.Family members of the shot person started arriving and were seen crying outside the shop.A woman in the centre management office said no robbery had taken place, but there had been a shooting. She would not give further details, saying a statement would be issued later.More to updates to follow as more information comes to light. Caxton News ServiceRead original story on rekordeast.co.za